ğŸ§© PHASE 4: Setup PostgreSQL Database (VERY EASY)
Step 1: Open pgAdmin OR Command Prompt
Login with postgres password

Step 2: Run these commands
CREATE DATABASE ewallet_db;
CREATE USER ewallet_user WITH PASSWORD 'ewallet_pass123';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE ewallet_db TO ewallet_user;


Done âœ…
ğŸ§© PHASE 5: Connect Spring Boot to Database

Open file:

src/main/resources/application.yml
Paste this:
spring:
  datasource:
    url: jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/ewallet_db
    username: ewallet_user
    password: ewallet_pass123

  jpa:
    hibernate:
      ddl-auto: update
    show-sql: true


Restart app:
mvn spring-boot:run
Spring Boot will auto-create tables ğŸ¯

